# -*-cperl-*-

=head1 NAME

CREATE_PNG - Create a PNG from the current Frame object.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This recipe creates a PNG file for each file in the current Frame
object. It will only work properly on 1-D or 2-D images, throwing a
warning if the input file is neither 1-D nor 2-D.

=head1 AUTHOR

Brad Cavanagh <b.cavanagh@jach.hawaii.edu>

=head1 COPYRIGHT

Copyright (C) 2009 Science and Technology Facilities Council. All
Rights Reserved.

=cut

foreach my $file ( $Frm->files ) {

  _CREATE_GRAPHIC_FROM_FILE_ FILE=$file TYPE=PNG ADDRES=1 XRES=256 YRES=256

}
